<section id="command-distance">
    <title>DISTANCE</title>
<indexterm><primary>DISTANCE</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>DISTANCE</command> <parameter>position</parameter></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the distance the turtle must travel along a straight line to reach the position given as the <parameter>position</parameter> input.
The <parameter>position</parameter> input must be a list containing two items, the X and Y coordinates.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
    <programlisting><userinput>SETPOS [0 0]
SHOW DISTANCE [0 100]</userinput>
100
<userinput>SHOW DISTANCE [300 400]</userinput>
500</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SETHEADING TOWARDS [300 400]
FORWARD DISTANCE [300 400]</userinput>
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>

</section>
